## 5. SEO Architecture

### Principle: Every page is unique, keyword-specific, and schema-marked.

### URL Structure

```
/                          → Homepage (target: "actual size on screen")
/[category]/               → /coins, /paper, /phones
/[category]/[slug]         → /coins/us-quarter, /paper/a4
/calibration               → Calibration guide (target: "how to calibrate screen")
/sitemap.xml               → Auto-generated
/robots.txt                → Auto-generated
```

### Per-Object SEO

Every object page gets:

| SEO element | Formula |
|---|---|
| `<title>` | `${object.meta.title} \| ActualSize` |
| `<meta description>` | `object.meta.description` (max 155 chars, stored in JSON) |
| `<h1>` | `object.meta.h1` (stored in JSON, human-written per object) |
| `og:title` | Same as `<title>` |
| `og:description` | Same as `<meta description>` |
| `og:image` | `/og/${category}/${slug}.png` (static, pre-generated) |
| `canonical` | Absolute URL of the page |
| `article:modified_time` | `object.meta.updatedAt` |

