## 6. Performance Architecture

### JavaScript Budget

| Script | Size | How loaded |
|---|---|---|
| `calibration-engine.ts` | < 6 KB (minified) | `type="module"` deferred |
| Everything else | 0 KB | Pure Astro/HTML/CSS |

**Total JS shipped to browser: < 6 KB.** This is non-negotiable.

### CSS Strategy

- All design tokens in `tokens.css` (loaded once via `BaseLayout`)
- No CSS-in-JS, no Tailwind JIT overhead
- Component styles are scoped via Astro's built-in `<style>` isolation
- Critical CSS is inlined by Astro's build step automatically

### Image Strategy

- Object images: `WebP` format, sized to max render dimension + 2× for retina
- `<img loading="lazy">` on all below-fold images
- `<img decoding="async">` on all images
- `width` and `height` attributes set on every `<img>` to prevent layout shift (CLS = 0)

### Font Strategy

```html
<!-- Preconnect first -->
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<!-- Load only the weights we use -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap">
```

### Build Output

Every page renders to a `.html` file. No SSR server, no edge functions needed. Deployable to any CDN in one command.

